{"name":"Mathlib.Topology.ContinuousFunction.Weierstrass","instances":[],"imports":["Init","Mathlib.Analysis.SpecialFunctions.Bernstein","Mathlib.Topology.Algebra.Algebra"],"declarations":[{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/ContinuousFunction/Weierstrass.lean#L121-L129","name":"exists_polynomial_near_of_continuousOn","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/ContinuousFunction/Weierstrass.html#exists_polynomial_near_of_continuousOn","doc":"Another alternative statement of Weierstrass's theorem,\nfor those who like epsilons, but not bundled continuous functions.\n\nEvery real-valued function `ℝ → ℝ` which is continuous on `[a,b]`\ncan be approximated to within any `ε > 0` on `[a,b]` by some polynomial.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/ContinuousFunction/Weierstrass.lean#L106-L112","name":"exists_polynomial_near_continuousMap","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/ContinuousFunction/Weierstrass.html#exists_polynomial_near_continuousMap","doc":"An alternative statement of Weierstrass' theorem,\nfor those who like their epsilons.\n\nEvery real-valued continuous function on `[a,b]` is within any `ε > 0` of some polynomial.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/ContinuousFunction/Weierstrass.lean#L93-L96","name":"continuousMap_mem_polynomialFunctions_closure","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/ContinuousFunction/Weierstrass.html#continuousMap_mem_polynomialFunctions_closure","doc":"An alternative statement of Weierstrass' theorem.\n\nEvery real-valued continuous function on `[a,b]` is a uniform limit of polynomials.\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/ContinuousFunction/Weierstrass.lean#L57-L86","name":"polynomialFunctions_closure_eq_top","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/ContinuousFunction/Weierstrass.html#polynomialFunctions_closure_eq_top","doc":"The **Weierstrass Approximation Theorem**:\npolynomials functions on `[a, b] ⊆ ℝ` are dense in `C([a,b],ℝ)`\n\n(While we could deduce this as an application of the Stone-Weierstrass theorem,\nour proof of that relies on the fact that `abs` is in the closure of polynomials on `[-M, M]`,\nso we may as well get this done first.)\n"},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Topology/ContinuousFunction/Weierstrass.lean#L35-L47","name":"polynomialFunctions_closure_eq_top'","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/ContinuousFunction/Weierstrass.html#polynomialFunctions_closure_eq_top'","doc":"The special case of the Weierstrass approximation theorem for the interval `[0,1]`.\nThis is just a matter of unravelling definitions and using the Bernstein approximations.\n"}]}